**[1861, 07-16] Ms.A.9.2.30.70**

RDW to [AWW]. 14pp.

Discusses Civil War. {Bulk of this passage in {u}BAA{/u}.} Sympathizes
with Italy.

He is surprised by the rapid reversals of nonresistances. “As far as its
professions go, the war on the part of the north is only an armed
attempt to punish traitors and to restore the Union to its former
dimensions.” Still he thinks most English support North, and he thinks
the war will end with abolition. “As to Italy you know that I am her
warm well wisher and feel a deep interest in all that concerns her.”


